data.text:
Title: Collin Co.

Author: Texas General Land Office

Date: ca. 1925

Medium: Lithograph

Condition: Excellent

Inches: 14 x 17 [Paper]

Centimeters: 35.56 x 43.18 [Paper]

Product ID: 3112076

Antique Texas county map published ca. 1925 by Wolf & Bennett for the Texas General Land Office. General Land Office maps show land patents, block and tract numbers, landowners, towns, railroads, and portions of adjacent counties where property boundaries extend beyond county limits.

This map shows Collin County, with the county seat of McKinney shown near its center. The north Texas county is traversed by a number of rail lines including the St. Louis & San Francisco Railroad, Houston & Texas Central Railroad, Missouri, Kansas & Texas Railroad, Gulf Colorado & Sante Fe Railroad, and the St. Louis & Southwestern Railroad. Collin County is bordered by Grayson, Fannin, Hunt, Denton, Dallas, and Rockwall counties.

Survey date – 1916
